// Isolated Zellij config for `cloudnav workspace`. Shipped under
//     <UserConfigDir>/cloudnav/zellij/config.kdl
// and selected at exec time via `zellij --config-dir`, so the user's
// own ~/.config/zellij stays completely untouched.
//
// Design intent: when you run `cloudnav workspace`, the resulting
// session should look and feel like Zellij — Zellij's native theme,
// keybindings, and chrome. cloudnav is just one of the panes inside
// the workspace, not a re-skinning of the multiplexer. We
// intentionally do NOT define a custom theme here; Zellij ships a
// solid default and most users have already tuned their preferred
// palette via terminal colours / installed Zellij themes elsewhere.
//
// What we do set:
//   - default_layout — points at our cloudnav.kdl multi-pane layout.
//   - mouse_mode true — most cloudnav users expect click-to-focus
//     across panes, matches the TUI's own click-to-select rows.
//   - copy_on_select true — yanking a value (project ID, ARN, sub
//     GUID) from any pane goes straight to the clipboard.
//
// Everything else inherits Zellij's defaults: the default theme,
// the default keybindings (Ctrl-p for pane mode, Ctrl-t for tab
// mode, Ctrl-h for help, etc.), the default status bar.

default_layout "cloudnav"
mouse_mode true
copy_on_select true
